From: Eric Dumazet <edumazet@google.com>
Date: Tue, 6 Mar 2018 07:54:53 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] l2tp: do not accept arbitrary sockets
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.15.15
Git-commit: 17cfe79a65f98abe535261856c5aef14f306dff7

[ Upstream commit 17cfe79a65f98abe535261856c5aef14f306dff7 ]

syzkaller found an issue caused by lack of sufficient checks
in l2tp_tunnel_create()

RAW sockets can not be considered as UDP ones for instance.

In another patch, we shall replace all pr_err() by less intrusive
pr_debug() so that syzkaller can find other bugs faster.
